name: Fawn Weaver
bio: L.A. bred. TN destined. CEO, Grant Sidney Inc. (owner of @unclenearest). @NYTimes bestselling author. @TED speaker. Married 20 yrs to my ❤️ @keithwvr.

social_posts.post_text:
Uncle Nearest Premium Whiskey announced that its sales exceeded $100 million through October 2022, with an on-track forecast to more than double that total by the end of 2023.

The company was founded by its CEO Fawn Weaver in 2017. She was then joined by Chief Business Officer Katharine Jerkens and, shortly after, Victoria Eady Butler, the great-great-granddaughter of the company’s namesake, Nearest Green.

Last year, Uncle Nearest announced it had become the best-selling Black American-founded, owned, and led spirit brand in U.S. history.  

Link in bio for more!

Introducing the Women of Uncle Nearest.

Most talk about diversity. We’re teaching a masterclass on it. Diversity in age, race, weight, socioeconomic upbringings, education, political affiliations, and everything else. 

Now, what publication is this photoshoot for? I guess you’ll just have to wait and see. 😜 But when your company is over 50% women, you do things different. You get stuff done. You don’t have time for nonsense. We’ve got work to do…together.

#WomenOfUncleNearest
#PurposeDrivenCompany
#UncleNearest

So…we bought a bank.

Actually, even better, we bought the building and became the landlord of Keith’s parent’s bank. 💪🏽🔥💃🏽

You want to know how women and people of color decrease the wealth gap? Real estate. 

Somewhere between living in my third homeless shelter, before the age of 19 (shout out to @covenant_house 🙏🏽) and coming into my own, I spent a lot of time reading biographies on America’s early titans like Andrew Carnegie, Henry Ford, Charles Schwab, Andrew Mellon, J.D. Rockefeller, J.P. Morgan. You want to know what they all had in common? Significant investments in real estate.

@keithwvr began with a condo in 1991, when he was only 18 (going to CSUN while working three jobs, he saved enough for the down payment). Then he leveraged that property and additional savings to buy two duplexes in 2000. Then, when we married in 2003, he taught me how to leverage our savings to buy additional real estate. Since then, we’ve bought and sold real estate as our main form of net worth for nearly 20 years. Of course, we could do what prior generations have done, and buy fancy, depreciating assets to floss… Or… we could do this and flex…focusing on passing down a legacy of generational wealth — debt free. 

We are the generation that knows better. So, we can do better. The Weavers are committed to doing better so the next generation isn’t starting from scratch. Want to join us?! 🙌🏽

#AppreciatingAssetsOnly 
#KnowBetterDoBetter
#DreamBigger
#FailHarder
#BuildGenerationalWealth

It’s time to let our HBCU’s SHINE like LIQUID GOLD in the Uncle Nearest #HBCUchallenge ! 🤩🎉

Beginning on MLK Jr. Day and extending through Black History Month (BHM) and Women’s History Month (WHM), Uncle Nearest is teaming up with retailers, outlets, restaurants and bars across America from January 16 to March 31, 2023, to raise $1 Million for Historically Black Colleges and Universities (HBCUs). 💰 Our most popular Uncle Nearest cocktail, around the world, is the Old Fashioned. So, now we're putting that Old Fashioned to work!

Here is how we WORK TOGETHER to make a real difference and continue to be #MoreThanWhiskey :

- 👉🏽 For every Uncle Nearest Old Fashioned sold at participating locations such as: restaurants, bars, hotels, outlets, amusement parks, and others listed on http://www.oldfashionedcocktail.com (link in bio), $1 will be donated to the challenge.
- 👉🏽 Uncle Nearest will donate $1 for each bottle of whiskey sold at participating online and brick-and-mortar retail stores.
- 👉🏽 @reservebarspirits will feature Uncle Nearest Old Fashioned Cocktail Kits, featuring a bottle of Uncle Nearest and bitters from @hellabittersandsoda , the Black-owned bitters and soda company. For every bundle sold, both Uncle Nearest and Reserve Bar will donate $1 to the challenge.
- 👉🏽 During the time period, our Whiskey Family can also submit a photo of a homemade Uncle Nearest Old-Fashioned at http://www.oldfashionedcocktail.com. Uncle Nearest will donate $1 for each image received.

We see the posts, stories, and direct-messages so we know our #WhiskeyFamily goes hard in the paint to spread the word. Let’s keep that same energy and HIT OUR GOAL as we continue to support the amazing educations of the leaders of tomorrow. 🎓

Remember, this Uncle Nearest #HBCUchallenge ends on March 31, 2023. So LET’S GET GOING! 💪🏽💯

For more information on the HBCU Old Fashioned Challenge, including a list of participating bars, restaurants, and retailers, and to follow along on the road to $1 million raised, please visit http://www.oldfashionedcocktail.com (link in bio).

Cheers, fam! And always #DrinkHonorably . 🥃❤️

Making Black History…AGAIN‼️🔥💪🏽

Making American History…PERIODT.

Go ahead and let it be known - IT’S OFFICIAL Y’ALL... 😲

Uncle Nearest continues shattering every record before us and is the “Most-Awarded Bourbon, Tennessee Whiskey and American Whiskey for 2022!” 💪🏽🏆

With 2019, 2020, and 2021 already under our belt, this marks 4 👏🏽 CONSECUTIVE👏🏽 YEARS👏🏽 of receiving this recognition, and we could not be any prouder!! 😄🎉 In 2022, we released some amazing Legacy Collection expressions, including 3 new Rye Whiskeys – Uncut/Unfiltered Master Blend Edition, 100-Proof Straight, and Single Barrel – as well as the highly sought-after Single Barrel Black Label at cask strength! 🔥

Coming in hot is one thing - we STAYED HOT throughout the year and managed to grab 230 TOTAL AWARDS! 🤩 Some notables among these awards are:

 - 🥇 2022 Master Blender of the Year- Whisky Magazine’s Icons of American Whiskey
 - 🥇 2022 Best in Bourbon- Great American International Spirits Competition
 - 🥇 Top 100 Spirits- Ultimate Spirits Challenge
 - 🥇 2022 Best in Class- Whiskies of the World
 - 🥇 2022 Double Gold- San Francisco World Spirits Competition
 - 🥇 2022 Master- The Spirits Business Global Luxury Masters

AND DON’T FORGET - Uncle Nearest is the ONLY AMERICAN WHISKEY to win 3 MASTERS AWARDS from The Spirits Business AND The Drinks Business Annual Autumn Blind Tasting! ❤️

YES, 2022 was an amazing year for Uncle Nearest and we can’t wait to see what 2023 has in store! For our #WhiskeyFamily that are making sure they #CompleteThe Collection, get ready to be blown away this year! 2023 is already setting out to be another award-winning, record-breaking, liquid gold-shinning year!

Continue to represent the #HBCUchallenge and help us raise $1,000,000 for HBCU across the nation! 

Link for HBCU CHALLENGE is in our BIO.

CHEERS, #WhiskeyFamily and 
Happy #BlackHistoryMonth !🥃💯 #BlingingInTheNewYear #morethanwhiskey #unclenearest

These eyes have turned my heart to mush for 20 years.

No, it’s not our anniversary. No, it’s not @keithwvr’s birthday.

It’s simply a great day to say, I’m a whole lotta woman to love…and this man has done it with perfection for nearly two decades.

He not only believes in me, he believes in letting me be me.

Out of the 4 billion women in the world, my personality type, INTJ (known as the the Architect or Mastermind) is the rarest for women. At only ~0.5% percent of the population, INTJ women are thought to be the rarest of any gender/type combination. It’s befitting my initials are FEW.

An INTJ loves solitude, craves silence, and gains the most energy being alone. Yet, my purpose in life has me in the world every day, with hundreds or thousands of people on the regular, and the juxtaposition between who I am naturally and what I was called to do, can be confusing for most.

But not him.

Keith Edward Weaver, I honor you. 

You are the greatest life partner, business partner, and best friend an enigma like me could ever have. You get me, somehow, without even trying. Loving me selflessly is innate to you. I don’t know how you do it, but you do it, consistently with consistency.

You are my love, my life, my rock.

UPDATE: With nearly 2,000 of you voting, the overwhelmingly clear favorites were #4 and #1. The third favorites were between 7, 6 and 2 — so my “official 3” are 4, 1 and 7…but 6 and 2 are wings. 😉 Thank you!!

Fam, I need you to help me choose my next press images again. 🙌🏽💪🏽

Choose your Top 3 favorites. Remember, this is for the press (magazines, newspapers, etc.), so which ones will look best in various publications.

Thank you much! Love y’all! ❤️❤️

THE DAY IS HERE! 😲 Humble Baron opens on 3/23/23! 🤩🎉Make sure you @humblebaronbar 🔥

Located at NEAREST GREEN DISTILLERY and clocking in at 518-feet, Humble Baron's 19-station bar will surpass the current WORLD’S LONGEST BAR by over 100 feet‼️You know how we roll at NGD...making history and shattering records is in our DNA! 💪🏽😄 We are bringing the 🔥🔥 with elevated dining, hand-crafted cocktails, and a culinary experience like NONE OTHER!! 💯 (Swipe through for pics of some of our favorites from the menu…so far!)

More than 17,000 square feet of dining luxury with a seating capacity of 500 people indoors and more than 15.000 outdoors, Humble Baron’s inspiration, @keithwvr, describes the venue as a place, “where EVERYONE has a seat at the table.” 👏🏽🙌🏽

As you'd expect, the cocktail program is 🔥 Crafted in partnership with Gin & Luck, the hospitality company behind renowned cocktail institution Death & Co. @deathandcompany with the cocktails curated by Director of Beverage @dajontherocks , even the non-alcoholic cocktail menu is not to be missed! 

James Beard nominee and critically acclaimed chef and television host @chefgarvin has crafted a culinary masterpiece with @chefjaycraddick at the helm. And wait until you see the live music portion of the venue, designed by the former technical engineer for Prince’s Paisley Park. Out of this world! EVERYTHING IS ELEVATED! 👌🏾

To celebrate its grand opening on Thursday, March 23, Humble Baron will debut with an official ribbon-cutting ceremony at 6pm CST followed by a live performance by Country Music Recording Artist, American Idol’s @huntergirlmusic . 🎶

The weekend celebrations WILL CONTINUE with a lineup of scheduled events, including performances by @neonunionmusic and DJ BOVA on Friday, Grown & Sexy day party by the Lifestyle Specialist, @kennyburns and DJ @callmebova on Saturday, followed by Sunday Gospel Brunch with Grown Folk Mimosas on tap‼️ 🥃🍾😋🍹The Weavers (@fawn.weaver and @keithwvr) will be at every opening event!! 

With more than 110,000 visitors to NGD in the past year alone, this highly anticipated opening of Humble Baron will rapidly become one of Tennessee’s most visited venues.

Sunday with the Weavers is FINALLY here‼️

Y’all, but we still have no desire to be on TV. At…all. Sorry! 😜

However, if you’ve ever thought to yourself, “I sure wish I could join the Weavers on Sundays with all that delicious soul food they eat and the scrumptious looking cocktails they drink, here’s your chance!

We’ll be at @humblebaronbar for every opening weekend event AND will cap off the extraordinary historic milestone (shattering the 25-year record for the world’s longest bar) with an afternoon of gratitude.

Join us on Sunday, March 26th at 1pm (after church, y’all‼️) at Humble Baron (HB) on the grounds of Nearest Green Distillery.

Our favorite worship leader of all time @iamkaiapineda will kick off the monthly Gospel Brunch series at HB and we could not be more excited! 🙏🏽💃🏽

The most successful Black owned distillery in the world has a chaplain? And his wife @iamkaiapineda is a pastor and worship leader? 🤷🏽‍♀️😉

The world’s longest bar is closing out its grand opening weekend with a Gospel Brunch series? 🥳🎉

Yes, yes and yes. Welcome to our home in the Bible Belt of America. 🙏🏽❤️🙏🏽

#DreamBigger #FailHarder #CementLegacies #MakeHistory #ShatterEveryRecord #MoreThanWhiskey #DrinkHonorably

Brace yourself for an adventure like no other‼️The unstoppable @fawn.weaver, the hardest-working CEO in spirits, is on a mission to honor and celebrate our brave armed forces. 🙏🏽⁣
⁣
Join her as she takes us BTS at some of the world's most heavily guarded military bases, including Fort Knox, the world's largest repository of gold ($300 Billion, y'all!), and the largest naval station in the world, Naval Station Norfolk. You how Langley constantly tracked Jason Bourne? 😜 Well, Fawn is going to see how they do that! The Pentagon, Naval Station Pearl Harbor, Camp Pendleton, Fort Bragg -- if it's historical, she's going. And more bases are being added to the schedule daily. 💥
⁣
If you followed @fawn.weaver on her 2022 CEO Thank You Tour, you know she visited Uncle Nearest top retailers, restaurants, bars, hotels, and entertainment centers in 121 Cities in 100 Days. In her 2021 Tour, she woke up in a new state every day to thank those who have helped make Uncle Nearest the world's most successful Black-owned and founded spirit brand of all time. 💃🏽
⁣
Fawn's 2023 CEO Tour, “𝘛𝘩𝘢𝘯𝘬 𝘠𝘰𝘶 𝘧𝘰𝘳 𝘠𝘰𝘶𝘳 𝘚𝘦𝘳𝘷𝘪𝘤𝘦, 𝘛𝘩𝘢𝘯𝘬 𝘠𝘰𝘶 𝘧𝘰𝘳 𝘠𝘰𝘶𝘳 𝘚𝘶𝘱𝘱𝘰𝘳𝘵,” is no ordinary tour. Fawn is rolling up her sleeves and getting to work. From working out with the US ARMY Physical Fitness Team at Fort Knox at 06:30 to meeting with commanding officers and generals, giving keynote addresses, attending a military ball, learning to shoot, and maybe even throwing grenades, she's going full-on G.I. Jane. 💪🏽⁣
⁣
The military has confirmed no other CEO has ever attempted to do what Fawn is geared up to do, beginning on 4/11, so make sure to cheer her on as she embarks on a journey to cheer on our troops! 👏🏽
⁣
Speaking of which, Fawn is inviting our #WhiskeyFamily to join her on this journey. Although she can't take you onto the military bases, you can join her for a toast to our armed forces at precisely 18:56 (6:56pm) throughout the tour. 🥃 Join her on IG Live OR EVEN BETTER, you can join her in person! 🔥⁣
⁣
Go to http://UncleNearest.com/1856-happy-hours/ or click the link in our bio to RSVP. More dates will be added, but the first 10 dates are live. 🥳

You want to know how @unclenearest will reach $200 Million in sales by the end of this year? It begins here. Every weekend, our veterans and our brave U.S. service men and women flood Nearest Green Distillery. Between 5,000-8,000 visitors every weekend and the percentage of those who are military and military families cannot even be counted. 🙏🏽🇺🇸

The military has supported us from Day One and propelled us to the #1 Black founded and owned spirits brand of all time. And we remain 100% independent. 💪🏽🔥

So, for the next four months, every week I am going base to base, thanking our military for helping us defy all odds and to do what most believed to be impossible in our country.

Every day, from sun up to sun down, I will be with the troops — doing everything from 06:30 (6:30am) workouts, to tandem jumping with expert paratroopers, to hopping in Destroyers, observing search and rescues, meetings at the Pentagon and Langley  and the list goes on and on.

At least once a week, I will host an 18:56 Happy Hour where we will raise a glass and salute our troops at exactly 18:56 (6:56pm EST). Tonight, meet me at Edge @edgetampa, the rooftop bar of the Epicurean Hotel @epicureanhotel any time after 6pm. We will raise a glass to the troops and America’s veterans, in acknowledgment that our freedom is not free; it has come at a great cost. 

If you want to join us from home, we’ll raise our glasses together on IG Live at exactly 18:56 (6:56pm).

Today, I am kicking of this 2023 #CEOThankYouTour at @macdillafb. If you are on base, I’m about to sign bottles at the Class Six Exchange and then you can meet me at 10am at the MacDill Air Force Base Theater, where I will be holding a fireside chat for our troops, alongside my incredible host for this tour on every base, @jwtrox, Senior Enlisted Advisor to the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff (SEAC).

To see my full tour schedule, please refer to the most recent post on IG.

To our honorable veterans and all our brave service men and women: Thank You for Your Service. Thank You for Your Support.

#DrinkHonorably #MoreThanWhiskey #CEOThankYouTour

It’s time to work out with our troops! “Competitor ready!” 💪🏽 The Army physical fitness trainer was told to create a competitive round for a group of Command Sergeant Majors. There was clearly a miscommunication somewhere… 🤣😂 But I’m here now, so let’s get after it! 🔥🔥

There is no greater honor than my annual #CEOThankYouTour, and this one is beyond special, for reasons you can imagine.

One thing I have discovered in going base to base is the military may be one of the most diverse employee groups in the world. It makes me feel great that so many of the brave service men and women of our country look like me. I feel very much at home on these bases.

I’ve got our Director of Emerging Markets, @smoothwhiskeydrew, working out with @jwtrox  and me, and our Kentucky State Manager, @richiemichaels1 on BTS. 🙌🏽

If you are in the Louisville area tonight, meet me at @corridorbarnulu at  6:30pm, where we will enjoy some apps and raise a glass of @unclenearest to salute our vets and honorable troops at exactly 18:56 (6:56pm EST). First round is on me. 💪🏽😉

This is us. This was Tuesday, at the NJAI Spirits on the Rise Summit, where we hosted 200+ BIPOC spirits founders and their ELTs at Nearest Green Distillery, and gave them the tools and understanding needed to take their businesses to the next level.

I shared with them my philosophy on competition: I don’t believe @unclenearest has any. Not because we’re the greatest that ever was…but because it’s my belief that my job is to make the pie bigger for every minority founder out there operating in excellence. And if I do my job right, and make the pie bigger…everyone eats. 

So, we gave them access to 40+ investors who write BIG checks. They were given the opportunity to meet with and showcase their brands to national accounts like @tupelohoneycafe, @hyatt, @tgifridays, and to the CEOs, Vice chairs and presidents of banks like JP Morgan Chase, Truist, Farm Credit, CapStar, and to leaders like the VP of Investment Banking at Goldman Sachs to the founder, CEO and president of ReserveBar.com.

The presidents of distribution companies were there and gave their advice and each one made themselves accessible to be pitched.

For two straight days, the powerhouse relationships we have built as @unclenearest has grown, we made accessible to these BIPOC founders. No one was off limits. Nothing like this has ever been done, in ANY INDUSTRY, and my hope is it will become the blueprint for every other industry lacking diversity in ownership. I could not be more excited for the futures of these founders and their brands after this Summit! To join us next year, keep your eyes on NearestandJack.org where we will soon announce the 2024 Summit dates.

But in the midst of all of this greatness, the world again stood still, as @keithwvr was photographed looking at me in a way only he can. I am proud of so many things that I do each day, but what I am most proud of, is I continue to do so much while keeping God, faith and my husband first. 

This is us. This has been us since 2003. This will be us until death do us part. 🙏🏽❤️

Doing what only our founder and CEO @fawn.weaver can do. 

Fawn’s schedule at the Pentagon today:

1. Meeting with the Sergeant Major of the Army, Michael A. Grinston. 

2. Meeting with Master Chief Petty Officer of the Navy, James Honea.

3. Lunch with the Senior Enlisted Advisor to Chairman (SEAC) of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, Ramón "CZ" Colón-López.

4. Meeting with the Master Chief Petty Officer of the Coast Guard, Heath B. Jones.

5. Meeting with United States Secretary of Defense, Lloyd Austin.

6. 18:56 Happy Hour salute to our troops at @1799prime_alexandria .

This followed early morning meetings with former Chief Master Sergeant of the Air Force, Kaleth Wright, and former Chief Master Sergeant, Manny Piñeiro.
Why are all the top leaders of our Armed Forces taking the time to meet with me? Because although she didn’t know it when this tour First began, she is the FIRST civilian CEO to take the time to go meet with the troops to support them, honor them and to simply say thank you and what can we do to help. 

And as we’ve been meeting with the troops and leadership, we’ve determined there is even more we can do. Stay tuned, our friends and family. One CEO plus all her CEO friends plus you…we’re about to do something that’s never before been done.

#CEOThankYouTour

Wednesday Word

I make no apologies for refusing to own another person’s lack. My purpose is too great.

Your purpose is too great.

So, go out and be great today…knowing you lack nothing that you need to succeed today (unless you don’t believe that, in which case, you are right).

#WednesdayWord

Guess who Harvard Business School is doing a business case on?! 🙋🏽‍♀️ When HBS professors come to do a case study on you, you’ve either done things REALLY right or really wrong. Guess which one it is for us?! 🥳

We went from nothing but dirt and a vision to already being one of the Top 10 Most Visited Distilleries in the World (and there are tens of thousands).

@unclenearest has made believers out of everyone. Those who expected us to fail: now believers. Those who were laying traps to try to trip us up and make us fail: now believers. Haters: still hating but now believers. 😂💪🏽😉 Those rooting for us from day one: still believers. 🙏🏽❤️🙏🏽

Bottom line: When God gives you a vision, rest assured you’ll have the resources to fulfill it.  No matter how tight money gets, no matter how high the hill may seem that you have left to climb, you ALWAYS have enough to complete the vision you’ve been assigned.

Oh yeah, and if you’ve not yet been to Nearest Green Distillery…what are you waiting  on?! A personal invitation? Welp, here you go! 🤩

#WellDoneGoodAndFaithfulServant

Don’t ever expect me to be like anyone else or you will be disappointed.

God’s imprint on my life is one-of-a-kind. You’ve never seen it before me and you’ll never see it again after me.

I am not one-dimensional, so don’t have an expectation that I will be the same way, in every circumstance. 

What you can expect from me in every situation is authenticity.

There is a side of me that is patient, incredibly loyal, loving, kind, gentle, giving, and roots for everyone. 😍❤️

Come for my family or team members and you will see a whole other side of me. You don’t want none of her. 💪🏽🔥

There is a side of me that is warm, fun-loving, sings and dances around with complete abandon, and remains open to all. 🤗🥳🥰

There is also a side that if you attempt to do me harm or double cross me in business, unfortunately, I know God will shut you down so fast that you won’t have time to realize what happened. I won’t say anything…I’ll just sit back and watch your life and business crumble, knowing that is what was inevitable. 🤷🏽‍♀️🙏🏽

The idea that a leader should be one way at all times is flawed. 

A leader who is authentic and transparent will show all genuine sides.

Multi-dimensional is something to be celebrated. What that means, is the person you are dealing with is a real one.

#NoCodeSwitching
#ComfyInMySkin
#KnowWhoYouAre
#EmbraceAuthenticity
#PurposeDrivenCEO
#UncleNearestCEO

5 failed IUIs, 4 failed IVF cycles, 2 failed adoptions and 1 failed surrogacy — parenthood wasn’t in the card for us. 

But @keithwvr emerged as a dependable father figure for so many; always there with a patient, listening ear and ready to dispense sage advice whenever someone is in need. 

To all the father figures out there, without your own biological children, I don’t want you to feel left out today.

Shout out/tag that incredible man you know, who is a father to so many who are not biologically their own, and let them know they are needed, they are necessary, and we honor them on this beautiful Father’s Day.

P.S. No need to send condolences for our parenthood journey. I promise you, we’ve always been good with whatever God chooses for our lives, and we are parents to so many…just not biologically, and we’re A-okay with that.

The three prayers I have prayed for more than 25 years.

After my first phone call with @keithwvr in May 2003, I prayed the “Box Me In” prayer. Nearly 20 years of an incredible marriage later, I am SO happy I did!

In 2020, when the world seemed to be descending FAST into the Apocalypse 😆 I regularly prayed the “PRAYER TO STAY FOCUSED ON THE NOW” so I could make the right decisions to grow @unclenearest during a time when most craft distilleries and brands were teetering on closure.

During the 2021-2022 global supply chain crisis, which hit us from every which way, I regularly prayed the “PRAYER TO KEEP FROM WORRYING” so I could spend every moment, of every day, focused exclusively on creative solutions and problem-solving.

The peace I have had in my life hasn’t come from a life of ease. I regularly set “impossible” goals and have to jump over more hurdles to get to a single one of those goals than most will in a lifetime. I take great risks to achieve even greater rewards. My life is purpose-driven, which means “ease” is not my path.

Something @50cent said to @oprah in an 2012 interview, when she asked if he feared for his life after having been shot 9 times, has stayed with me and I’ve shared it with so many people who have asked about my peace. Every time I even CONSIDER worrying about something, I am reminded of his words and Oprah’s enlightened  response, “Oooh, that is good!” 

His response was that he didn’t worry: “Either pray or worry; don’t do both. If you’re going to sit there and say a prayer, and THEN worry, how do you think God feels…?”

It’s been a tough first half of 2023 for many of you. My prayer is you will keep these three prayers (and the words of the Prophet 50 Cent 😆) in your mind arsenal at all times so the, “.. peace that surpasses all understanding will guard your hearts and your minds…”

Now, go out and MAKE IT a great day!

#PurposeDrivenCEO
#UncleNearestCEO
#FocusOnTheNow
#ItsBiggerThanYou

What I am doing has not been done in over two centuries.

What I am doing has never before been accomplished by a woman.

What I am doing has never been accomplished by a person of color, especially an African American.

It is why you will never hear me complain.

I’m am too busy doing the work of my Father in heaven, honoring my earthly father who is now in heaven, and achieving what my ancestors would have done if they’d been given the ability to pursue their dreams. 

No one can tell me what I cannot do. 

Speaking and living with my level of confidence causes some (very very few…but still) internet trolls to suggest I “move in silence” and some see it as arrogance. Anyone who knows me knows there is not an arrogant bone in my body.

But I will not dumb down the gifts and talents God has given me to make others comfortable with their decisions to shrink.

Every day of my life is living proof that anyone, can do anything, no matter where they begin — and I will spend my life shouting that from the mountaintops around the world — so women and people of color believe NOW is the time to take the cap off.

How do I know?

I left home at 15 years old.

Lived with no money between the projects of Watts and three homeless shelters by 18 years old.

Not a single penny or property I own was given to me. 

Rising from the ashes, over and over again, is all I’ve ever known.

I don’t even know how to code-switch.

To live out every single day with purpose, I must live out loud.

I learned years ago that I cannot please God and please all people. Nor is that my responsibility.

I am 1 out of 8,045,311,447.

I am 1 of 1.

I am 100% myself at all times, in all circumstances. For anyone looking for a real, authentic, true cup of tea...

It’s the only kind I serve.

Don’t let my cool fro distract you from these words 😂 — it’s braid day. But it’s also my Sabbath, even though it’s a Wednesday.

I firmly uphold all 10 commandments. There has long been debate about whether the Sabbath is still required or not. I have no intention of delving into that discussion. I’ll leave that to the Bible scholars.

What I know for sure is that of the 10 commandments, nine of them benefit others. It’s the 10th one — resting a full 24 hours a week — that benefits me. It renews and refreshes me, keeping my mind sharp, allowing me to accomplish more in six days than most do in months, if not years.

I made two commitments to the Lord 26 years ago. The first is that I would always tithe. The second is that I would always observe the Sabbath.

I’ve faithfully honored those commitments, without fail, and I believe that so many of my life’s blessings are a direct result of that. The greatest of those blessings is a worry-free, peaceful life — both in business and personally.

I’ll share my tips for remaining worry-free and maintaining a peaceful life on another day, but for today, I rest.

This is 20. This is us.

- 20 years of unconditional love
- 20 years of the highest respect
- 20 years of being best friends
- 20 years filled with hearty laughter
- 20 years of enjoyment
- 20 years of nurturing each other’s growth
- 20 years of encouraging individual evolution
- 20 years of adoration
- 20 years of prioritizing each other
- 20 years of pure joy
- 20 years of partnership in business and life
- 20 years of respecting who we are and supporting who we’re destined to become
- 20 years of setting aside pride and ego to foster a communication style grounded in respect, honor, friendship and trust

Twenty years ago today, my life went from great to extraordinary when I evolved from Ms. Wilson to Mrs. Weaver. Now, twenty years later, it just keeps getting better. Like fine wine, our love matures with time.

Society often paints marriage as a challenge, hard work, maybe even impossible to be happy in. But I’ve always rejected that notion. I still do. 

Because I chose the right partner, I’ve found the truth in the saying, “If you love what you do, you’ll never work a day in your life.” That’s exactly how I feel about my marriage. 

Loving, adoring, and respecting my spouse makes being his partner feel like the greatest honor.

This is the only kind of marriage I know. So, no one can tell me a marriage this beautiful and amazing isn’t possible.

Our marriage isn’t for the Gram. 

It’s real. Real love. As my California license plate frame once said, and still holds true in Tennessee, “I Love My Life As K. Weaver’s Wife.”

To those wondering if a great, enjoyable, lasting, and happy marriage is still possible:

If He did it before,
He can do it again.
Same God right now,
Same God back then.
